:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:147:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/a-sneak-peek-at-events-calendar-6-0/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Jul 2022 17:19:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"What\'s New\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2449942\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:619:\"<p>Around this time last year, we published an article describing the history of a complex project that our team had been facing for a long time. Since then, we&#8217;ve worked tirelessly to finish renovating the system that handles recurring events and other components in our plugins. We&#8217;re now very close to rolling out the long-awaited&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/a-sneak-peek-at-events-calendar-6-0/\">A Sneak Peek at Events Calendar 6.0&nbsp;</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"Lauren\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11498:\"\n<p>Around this time last year, <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/how-we-finally-tackled-the-massive-project-we-were-putting-off-and-how-you-can-too/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">we published an article</a> describing the history of a complex project that our team had been facing for a long time. Since then, we&#8217;ve worked tirelessly to finish renovating the system that handles recurring events and other components in our plugins. We&#8217;re now very close to rolling out the long-awaited Events Calendar 6.0, the biggest release in our plugin’s 13-year history.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This update will bring major improvements to both The Events Calendar and Events Calendar Pro, including enhanced performance, better event data storage, and a brand new system to manage recurring events, including a new post-type called “Series.” Here’s a sneak peek at everything to come!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-improvements-to-recurring-events-in-events-calendar-pro\">Improvements to recurring events in Events Calendar Pro <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/26a1.png\" alt=\"⚡\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Recurring events are one of the most popular features in <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/products/wordpress-events-calendar/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Events Calendar Pro</a>, and after years of working to improve recurring event functionality, this release will bring a major overhaul to the creation and management of recurring events in our plugins.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Recurring events will adhere to the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/2000/01/foo.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">iCalendar Standard</a>, and you can edit and update them in line with what you’re used to in applications like Google Calendar or Outlook. This means you can now make changes to a single recurring event, all recurring events, or only upcoming events without divorcing those events from the group.</li><li>Recurring events will only be listed once in the wp-admin dashboard, making it easy to edit all occurrences in one place. And if you&#8217;d like to see each recurring event listed individually you can access them in the Events Manager.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>It took a great deal of development work to get this functionality working seamlessly, and we&#8217;re proud of our team of devs who worked tirelessly through the many obstacles that only geeks can fully understand.&nbsp;</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>This leads us to the next big improvement coming to Events Calendar Pro….</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-the-new-series-feature-for-grouping-events-in-events-calendar-pro\">The new “Series” feature for grouping events in Events Calendar Pro <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/26a1.png\" alt=\"⚡\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sometimes, a recurring event is straightforward: Karaoke night every Tuesday. A meeting every other Thursday. A birthday once a year.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other times, recurring events don’t follow simple rules. Enter Series: A new post-type that provides a powerful way to group, organize and present events. A Series is completely customizable and can contain any single or recurring event. Each occurrence can include a different agenda, venue, or host. You can add different events to a series, even if they aren’t part of a recurring event.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Each Series also has its own <a href=\"https://series-demo.theeventscalendar.com/series/kids-camp/?eventDisplay=list\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">landing page</a> where users can see all related events in one place. This can come in handy in a variety of ways. For example, admins can have different featured images for each event in the series, then use the Photo View or List View to display a beautiful visual landing page of related events!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-has-background\"><a href=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM.png\"><img width=\"665\" height=\"471\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-665x471.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2449984\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-665x471.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-300x213.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-120x85.png 120w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-768x544.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1536x1089.png 1536w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-2048x1452.png 2048w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-430x305.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-645x457.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-2000x1418.png 2000w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1068x757.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-460x326.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1602x1136.png 1602w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1074x761.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-512x363.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1611x1142.png 1611w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-1555x1102.png 1555w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-707x501.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-600x425.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/Screen-Shot-2022-07-07-at-3.12.56-PM-500x354.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Series can have different attributes such as different locations for the same Blood Drive. Using the Map view, admins can create a nice visual display of where each occurrence of the event will take place!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-style-has-background\"><a href=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1.png\"><img width=\"665\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-665x425.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2449972\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-665x425.png 665w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-300x192.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-133x85.png 133w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-768x490.png 768w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-430x274.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-645x412.png 645w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-1068x682.png 1068w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-460x294.png 460w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-1074x686.png 1074w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-512x327.png 512w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-707x451.png 707w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-600x383.png 600w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1-500x319.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-1.png 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are so many potential use cases for this neat new post-type. You can learn more about Series and the updates to recurring events <a href=\"https://series-demo.theeventscalendar.com/whats-new/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here</a>, plus check out a <a href=\"https://series-demo.theeventscalendar.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">demo calendar with various examples of Series.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-the-highly-requested-duplicate-event-tool-events-calendar-pro\">The highly-requested Duplicate Event tool (Events Calendar Pro <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/26a1.png\" alt=\"⚡\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" />)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many of you have <a href=\"https://app.productstash.io/the-events-calendar-suite-roadmap?idea=604fce79488599002bd746c8&amp;utm_source=ActiveCampaign&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=%E2%8F%B1%EF%B8%8F+Get+Ready+for+Our+Biggest+Release+in+History&amp;utm_campaign=Early+June+2022+Newsletter+-+ECP+6+0+On+the+Horizon#ideas\">asked for an easy way to clone events</a>, and we heard you. The latest Events Calendar Pro release will include a slick new Duplicate Event tool that takes the busywork out of copying existing events.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-has-background\"><img width=\"500\" height=\"408\" src=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2449987\" srcset=\"https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3.png 500w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3-300x245.png 300w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3-104x85.png 104w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3-430x351.png 430w, https://images.theeventscalendar.com/uploads/2022/07/image-3-460x375.png 460w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-a-better-behind-the-scenes-experience-the-events-calendar-and-events-calendar-pro\">A better behind-the-scenes experience (The Events Calendar and Events Calendar Pro <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/26a1.png\" alt=\"⚡\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" />)</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve overhauled the event data storage system and made performance enhancements on the backend for The Events Calendar and Events Calendar Pro. This means a better experience for both event creators and attendees. Load times will be faster in the admin dashboard and in the calendar view for users on the frontend.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-take-it-for-a-spin\">Take it for a Spin!</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#8217;ve released several beta versions and invite you to test drive Events Calendar Pro 6.0 Beta today. The beta version is free and available to all users. <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/sign-up-to-be-a-beta-tester/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Sign up and download the beta today</a>, and help us with feedback as we wrap up development.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’re looking forward to getting this new and improved version into your hands. Keep an eye out for the official launch of Events Calendar 6.0 coming very soon.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/blog/news/a-sneak-peek-at-events-calendar-6-0/\">A Sneak Peek at Events Calendar 6.0&nbsp;</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"The Events Calendar 5.16.2.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:164:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-16-2-1/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 08 Jul 2022 17:13:59 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"The Events Calendar\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2450254\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:612:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This latest version of The Events Calendar features a quick fix to a conflict with our datepicker. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixed Bugs that were squashed in this release: We now don&#8217;t load Event Aggregator scripts on&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-16-2-1/\">The Events Calendar 5.16.2.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1627:\"\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of The Events Calendar features a quick fix to a conflict with our datepicker.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/2705.png\" alt=\"✅\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em; max-height: 1em;\" /> Fixed</h4>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\">Bugs that were squashed in this release:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>We now don&#8217;t load Event Aggregator scripts on post edit pages, to prevent datepicker conflicts.</li><li>Added filter: <code>aggregator_should_load_scripts</code></li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/the-events-calendar/the-events-calendar-5-16-2-1/\">The Events Calendar 5.16.2.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"Events Calendar Pro 5.14.3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:162:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-5-14-3/?utm_source=theeventscalendar&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=rss-feed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 06 Jul 2022 18:06:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"Events Calendar Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"release notes\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=2448197\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:601:\"<p>Summary Maintenance Release This latest version of Events Calendar Pro improves upon the navigation when using Photo view on the main events page. As always, we recommend testing updates on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing. ✅ Fixed Bugs that were squashed in this release: Ensure the Next arrow in&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-notes/events-calendar-pro/events-calendar-pro-5-14-3/\">Events Calendar Pro 5.14.3</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Jaime\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1748:\"\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.3%\">\n<h3 id=\"h-summary\">Summary</h3>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"release-label has-normal-font-size\">Maintenance Release</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\">\n<p class=\"release-summary__overview has-medium-font-size\">This latest version of Events Calendar Pro improves upon the navigation when using Photo view on the main events page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, we recommend <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/knowledgebase/k/creating-and-using-a-wordpress-staging-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">testing updates</a> on a staging site first, but it should all be smooth sailing.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\">\n<h4 id=\"h-fixed\"><img s